			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Metal Fragment</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">金属碎片</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Metal pieces; Metal Ore; Metal remnants</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Metal pieces; Metal Ore; Metal remnants</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Emissions</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Metal and semimetal elements and ions</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">A metal fragment is a piece of a larger item that cannot be identified, or that is less than 50% of the original item. Metal pieces that have been exposed to the environment may rust depending upon their material. Metal Fragments are a type of resource, used mainly in the crafting of various items or as a building material in player made structures. The main, and by far easiest and safest way to obtain metal fragments are to mine Metal Ore from Rocks, then smelt the ore using a Furnace or Large Furnace.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">金属碎片是指无法辨认的较大物品的碎片，或小于原物品 50%的碎片。暴露在环境中的金属碎片可能会生锈，这取决于其材质。金属碎片是一种资源，主要用于制作各种物品或作为玩家建筑的建筑材料。获得金属碎片的主要方法，也是目前最简单、最安全的方法是从岩石中开采金属矿石，然后使用熔炉或大型熔炉熔炼矿石。</common:generalComment>
			<sumFormula>Varies based on the type of metal</sumFormula>
